# Nielsen Heuristics (UI)

Apply Jakob Nielsen's 10 usability heuristics to every UI change. Complements `visual-identity.mdc`, `html-standards.mdc`, `javascript-standards.mdc`, and `ui-elements-catalog.mdc`.

## Checklist (all 10)

| # | Heuristic | In this project |
|---|-----------|-----------------|
| 1 | **Visibility of system status** | Show loading, saving, upload, and render progress. Update status panel values. Disable buttons while async work runs; restore on completion or error. |
| 2 | **Match system and real world** | Use domain terms: Project, Media, Clip, Timeline, Render, Preview. Prefer NLE-familiar layout (library left, timeline bottom, properties right). |
| 3 | **User control and freedom** | Provide cancel/close for dialogs and long operations. Support deselect (click empty area). Never block navigation without an exit. |
| 4 | **Consistency and standards** | Reuse `btn`, `panel`, theme tokens, and icon sprite patterns. Same control behavior on main window and editor. |
| 5 | **Error prevention** | Confirm destructive actions (delete project, remove clip). Disable invalid actions instead of failing silently. Validate inputs before API calls. |
| 6 | **Recognition rather than recall** | Label buttons and panel headers. Show filenames, durations, and clip names on screen — do not rely on memory. Use `title` on truncated text. |
| 7 | **Flexibility and efficiency** | Support drag-and-drop where natural (media → timeline). Prefer keyboard-friendly focus order; add shortcuts only when they match common NLE habits. |
| 8 | **Aesthetic and minimalist design** | One primary action per panel header. Hide advanced fields until needed. No decorative chrome — every element earns its space. |
| 9 | **Help users recover from errors** | Surface errors in the UI (status text, inline message) — not `alert()`. State what failed and a next step (retry, check connection). |
| 10 | **Help and documentation** | Empty states explain what to do next ("Drop files here", "No projects yet"). Use `title`/`aria-label` on icon-only controls. |

## Examples

```html
<!-- ❌ BAD — no status, icon-only with no label -->
<button id="exportBtn"><svg class="icon">…</svg></button>

<!-- ✅ GOOD — labeled, disabled while busy -->
<button id="exportBtn" class="btn btn-primary" disabled aria-busy="true">Exporting…</button>
```

```javascript
// ❌ BAD — silent failure, no feedback
catch (e) {}

// ✅ GOOD — visible error, actionable message
catch (e) {
    console.error('Export failed', e);
    UI.setStatus('Export failed — check MLT status and try again.');
}
```

## Review before finishing UI work

- Can the user tell what the app is doing right now?
- Can they undo, cancel, or leave without losing unrelated work?
- Are labels, icons, and errors understandable without prior context?
